---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const siteName = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_SITE_NAME ?? "PricingNest";
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`MRR (Monthly Recurring Revenue) | ${siteName}`}
  description="MRR definition, how to calculate it, and what to watch when modeling pricing changes."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>MRR (Monthly Recurring Revenue)</h1>
    <p>MRR is the recurring revenue you expect to earn each month from subscriptions and recurring contracts.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="grid">
    <article class="card col8">
      <h2>How to calculate MRR</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><strong>Simple</strong>: sum of monthly subscription revenue across active customers.</li>
        <li><strong>Annual plans</strong>: convert to monthly (annual price / 12) to keep apples-to-apples comparisons.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage</strong>: treat predictable recurring minimums as MRR; keep volatile overages separate if they swing heavily.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Common pitfalls</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Counting one-time onboarding fees as MRR.</li>
        <li>Mixing billed revenue (cash) with run-rate revenue (MRR).</li>
        <li>Ignoring discounts, downgrades, and churn when projecting growth.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Tools to use</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/mrr-calculator/">MRR calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/arr-calculator/">ARR calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/churn-impact-calculator/">Churn impact calculator</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <aside class="card col4">
      <h2>Related terms</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/glossary/arr/">ARR</a></li>
        <li><a href="/glossary/churn/">Churn</a></li>
        <li><a href="/glossary/unit-economics/">Unit economics</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

